Iron Fist									KEY:Iron Tyrant ~ Iron Fist							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Antipaladin Class Features.IronTyrantClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																		DEFINE:IronTyrantIronFistBaseDice|0	DEFINE:IronTyrantIronFistBaseDiceSize|0	DEFINE:IronTyrantIronFistLVL|0							DESC:An iron tyrant gains Improved Unarmed Strike as a bonus feat. In addition, whenever the iron tyrant makes a successful attack with a gauntlet, spiked gauntlet, or armor spikes, the weapon damage is based on his level and not the weapon type, as per the warpriest's sacred weapon ability (%1d%2).|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDice|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDiceSize																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Improved Unarmed Strike																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDice|1+min(1,IronTyrantIronFistLVL/20)|PREBASESIZELT:M	BONUS:VAR|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDice|1+min(1,IronTyrantIronFistLVL/15)|PREBASESIZEEQ:M	BONUS:VAR|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDice|1+min(2,((IronTyrantIronFistLVL+5)/10))|PREBASESIZEGT:M	BONUS:VAR|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDiceSize|if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<5,4,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<10,6,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<15,8,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<20,10,6))))|PREBASESIZELT:M	BONUS:VAR|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDiceSize|if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<5,6,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<10,8,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<15,10,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<20,6,8))))|PREBASESIZEEQ:M	BONUS:VAR|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDiceSize|if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<5,8,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<10,6,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<15,8,if(IronTyrantIronFistLVL<20,6,8))))|PREBASESIZEGT:M	BONUS:VAR|IronTyrantIronFistLVL|AntipaladinLVL																									SOURCEPAGE:p.4	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|Gauntlets, spiked gauntlets, and armor spikes deal %1d%2|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDice|IronTyrantIronFistBaseDiceSize
Bonus Feats									KEY:Iron Tyrant ~ Bonus Feats							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Antipaladin Class Features.IronTyrantClassFeatures.SpecialQuality																																																																																																														DESC:At 3rd level and every 3 antipaladin levels thereafter, an iron tyrant gains a bonus feat in addition to those gained from normal advancement. This feat must be a combat feat that relates to the iron tyrant's armor or shield, such as Shield Focus, or one of the armor mastery feats on page 16.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Iron Tyrant Bonus Feat|AntipaladinLVL/3																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Unstoppable									KEY:Iron Tyrant ~ Unstoppable							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Antipaladin Class Features.IronTyrantClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																											DESC:When wearing heavy armor, an iron tyrant is not slowed by terrain that halves movement (such as dense rubble, light undergrowth, and shallow bogs). Terrain that has been magically manipulated to impede motion or terrain that reduces movement by more than half still affects him.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Fiendish Bond								KEY:Iron Tyrant ~ Fiendish Bond						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Antipaladin Class Features.IronTyrantClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																																																																																																												DESC:Instead of forming a fiendish bond with his weapon or a servant, an iron tyrant can form a bond with his armor. As a standard action, an iron tyrant can enhance his armor by calling upon a fiendish spirit's aid. This bond lasts for %1 minutes. When called, the spirit causes the armor to shed unholy light like a torch.|AntipaladinLVL	DESC:The spirit grants the armor a +%1 enhancement bonus. These bonuses stack with existing armor enhancement bonuses to a maximum of +5, or they can be used to add any of the following armor special abilities: dastard, ghost touch, fortification (heavy, light, or medium), invulnerability, spell resistance (13, 15, 17, or 19). Adding these special abilities consumes an amount of bonus equal to the special ability's base price modifier. In addition, the iron tyrant can grant his armor the unrighteous special ability at the cost of a +4 bonus. These special abilities are added to any special abilities the armor already has, but duplicate abilities do not stack. If the armor is not magical, at least a +1 enhancement bonus must be added before any other special abilities can be added. The bonus and special abilities granted by the spirit are determined when the spirit is called and cannot be changed until the spirit is called again.|min(6,(AntipaladinLVL-2)/3)|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=5	DESC:The fiendish spirit imparts no bonuses if the armor is worn by anyone other than the iron tyrant, but it resumes giving bonuses if the iron tyrant dons the armor again. An iron tyrant can use this ability %1 times per day. If a suit of bonded armor with a fiendish spirit is destroyed, the iron tyrant loses the use of this ability for 30 days, or until he gains a level, whichever comes first. During this 30-day period, the iron tyrant takes a -1 penalty on attack rolls and weapon damage rolls.|min(4,(AntipaladinLVL-1)/4)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.5

